Research skills focus
Evaluation

Evaluation is a fundamental research skill that involves systematically assessing the quality, credibility, and significance of a researcher's own research findings and methodologies. It requires researchers to critically examine the strengths and weaknesses of their work by applying rigorous criteria and standards. Through careful evaluation of their experiments, researchers can ensure the validity and reliability of their conclusions, identify potential biases or limitations, and make informed judgments about the value and impact of their research.
